The '''School of Archaeology''' is an [[academic department]] of the [[University of Oxford]] comprising the [[Institute of Archaeology (Oxford)|Institute of Archaeology]] and the [[Research Laboratory for Archaeology and the History of Art]] (RLAHA).<ref name=school>{{cite web|title=About the School|access-date=17 April 2018||website=School of Archaeology, University of Oxford|url=http://www.arch.ox.ac.uk/aboutus.html}}</ref> The two departments were merged in 2000 and the merged department is part of Oxford's [[Social Sciences Division, University of Oxford|Social Sciences Division]]. The current head of school is [[Julia Lee-Thorp]].<ref name=school/>
